article.headline: Longwood 77, Texas-Pan American 61
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Dana Smith and Kevin Swecker scored 13 points apiece to lead Longwood in a 77-61 win over Texas-Pan American on Wednesday night. Billy Robinson added 12 points for the Lancers (14-10), who have won seven straight games. Emmanuel Jones recorded a double-double for the Broncs (6-16), scoring 17 points and grabbing 10 boards. Nathan Hawkins added 12 points for UTPA, which has lost seven of its last eight. The game was close early, and the Broncs led 18-17 with 8:26 to go before halftime. But the Lancers went on a 21-10 run from there, taking a 36-28 lead at the break and staying ahead for the entire second frame. Longwood scored 24 points off 26 UTPA turnovers, and hit 8 of 23 shots from beyond the arc. The Broncs hit just 2 of 12 from long range.
